Description: Linux Bluetooth Remote Control
 Allows a J2ME device to control the Linux PC. This application allows:
    * injection of mouse/keyboard events into the kernel
    * execution of custom commands (commandline + dbus)
      one example for the dbus controller: control rhythmbox from your phone
    * remote volume control
    * controlling a mplayer instance
